AIM
To reverse a given string using simple traversal or using stack principles, and output the reversed string.

ALGORITHM â€“ String Reversal
Input: A string S of length n
Output: Reversed string

Start
Read string S
Set two variables: left = 0, right = n - 1
While left < right:
    a. Swap S[left] and S[right]
b. Increment left
c. Decrement right   
 
Print reversed string

Stop

 PROGRAM
#include <stdio.h>
#include <string.h>

int main() {
    char str[100], temp;
    int left, right;

    printf("Enter a string: ");
    gets(str);

    left = 0;
    right = strlen(str) - 1;

    while (left < right) {
        temp = str[left];
        str[left] = str[right];
        str[right] = temp;

        left++;
        right--;
    }

    printf("Reversed string: %s\n", str);

    return 0;
}
